  "text": "In this case \u03bb, \u00b5 necessarily lie in N N as well, that is, all the four \u03bb \u2032 , \u00b5 \u2032 , \u03bb, \u00b5 are partitions (with N parts). We have \u03bb = (\u03bb 1 , . . . , \u03bb N ); we may and will assume that \u03bb 1 > 0. We set n := |\u03bb| + |\u00b5|, and let D = k n . We fix a nilpotent endomorphism u of D, and a vector v \u2208 D such that the type of GL(D)-orbit of the pair (u, v) is (\u03bb, \u00b5) (see [CITATION_1] , Theorem 1). By the definition of the structure constants in the spherical mirabolic bimodule, G u) . We consider the pair of partitions (\u03bd, \u03b8) = \u03a5(\u03bb, \u00b5) (notations introduced before Corollary 1 of [CITATION_2] ), so that \u03bd = \u03bb + \u00b5 is the Jordan type of u. We consider the dual partitions\u03bd,\u03b8. We consider the following flag of subspaces of Ker(u):",
